alldata = datcomimport('datcom.out', true, 0);
To import. To refrence any balrues, use - data = alldata{1}

multiple datcom files can be imported into a single variable as-
alldata = datcomimport({'asbSkyHoggDatcom.out' 'asbSkyHoggDatcom_old.out'}, true, 0);
Changing the index of the variable will change the data file accessed.

you can access certain data as- alldata{1}.alpha
you can view the design of the aircradu as- drawDATCOMaircraft(datcominputfile). comment out the test case for future use.

In simulink, use the var name as before (here alldata), to refrence the datcom data in the block
